      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">5. Name your tags</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Name your header and footer with <code>id</code> like <code>&lt;div id="header"&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;div id="footer"&gt;</code></li>
          <li>Name your features with <code>class</code> like <code>&lt;div class="card"&gt;</code></li>
          <li>Name your buttons with <code>class</code> like <code>class="btn"</code> and use the class <code>.input</code></li>
          <li>Then add this nice CSS code</li>
        </ul>
<pre><code>
#header{
  text-align: center;
  background-image: linear-gradient(-225deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.2) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.6) 50%), url("images/shanghai.jpg");
  background-size: cover;
  padding: 150px;
  color: white;
}

.card{
  padding: 50px;
  font-weight: lighter;
  background-color: white;
  text-align:center;
  width:200px;
}

#footer{
  padding: 50px;
  background: rgb(30, 30, 30);
  color: lightgrey;
  text-align: center;
  line-height: 2;
}

#footer ul {
  padding-left:0;
  list-style: none;
}

#footer li {
  display: inline-block;
  padding:0px 10px;
}

.input {
  font-size: 18px;
  height:50px;
  padding:0px 15px;
  background:white;
  border:1px solid lightgray;
  width:200px;
  border-radius:3px;
}

.btn {
  background:#D42C14;
  color:white;
  font-weight: bolder;
  width:150px;
  border:1px solid #AB2513;
}

.btn:hover {
  background:#AB2513;
  color:white;
}
</code></pre>
